        "Every time I feel good about myself, something happens — a comment, a failure, a comparison — and I'm back at zero. There's no floor. The progress evaporates and I start over, and the starting-over is becoming more exhausting than the work itself. I keep looking for a way through.",
        "I don't know if I like myself. I know I'm supposed to, I know it's healthy, I know it's foundational. But when I sit quietly and ask the question honestly, the answer I get back is uncertain. I'm still looking for the person I'm supposed to be proud of. I manage, mostly.",
        "Other people seem to have an interior life that is rich and consistent and sure of itself. Mine feels like weather — changing unpredictably, difficult to trust, not something I can rely on to be the same tomorrow as it was today. The feeling is always there even when I don't talk about it.",
        "I got a lot of praise for things that made me perform, and very little for things that made me feel. So I grew up believing the performing was the valuable part, the feeling was the cost. I've spent years trying to reverse that accounting. The waiting itself becomes the weight.",
