        "I compare my internal experience to others' external presentation and find myself lacking. I know the comparison is unfair, that I'm seeing their highlight reel against my behind-the-scenes. I know this. I do it anyway. The knowing hasn't made it stop. I keep looking for the way through and haven't found it.",
        "There's a way I speak to myself in my head that I would consider cruel if someone else said it to me. But because it's my own voice, it has access that other voices don't — it knows exactly where to press, and it presses there often. I keep going.",
