        "I'm not sure if the self I present is protecting a real self underneath, or if the presented self has become so practised that the real one has atrophied. I'm afraid to find out. The uncertainty is its own kind of loneliness. I haven't given up on finding a different way through.",
        "I have always needed external validation to feel okay about myself, and I know how precarious that is — that it puts my wellbeing in other people's hands. I'm aware this is dangerous. I still need it. The awareness doesn't make the need go away. I keep going through the motions.",
        "People who grew up with secure attachment seem to have a basic confidence I can't access. They seem to trust that they're okay, that they'll be okay, that things will work out. I've never had that baseline. Everything feels contingent. I'm still figuring out what to do with all of this.",
        "I've sabotaged good things because I didn't feel I deserved them. Not consciously, not with intention, but looking back I can see the pattern — the relationship I pushed away, the opportunity I didn't pursue, the kindness I deflected. I see it and I don't know how to stop. It stays quiet.",
        "I read self-help books about self-worth the way some people read instruction manuals — looking for the specific steps, the technique that will fix the thing. The books are fine. The thing doesn't respond to books the way I wish it would. I keep waiting for something to change and it hasn't.",
        "There are moments — rare, but real — when I feel okay about being who I am. Not excellent, not proud, just okay. I'm trying to extend those moments, to notice them more often, to let them count. They're data. I'm trying to update on the data. Day by day.",
