        "I told someone the truth about my self-doubt and they laughed — not at me, but with recognition. They thought I'd always been confident. The image I project and the internal reality are not the same document. Some days I get it almost right and then it falls apart again and I start over.",
        "I've been practising asking for things without feeling guilty about the asking. Small things first. The practice is extending. The asking itself is an act of self-worth, a claim that what I need is legitimate. I've been here for a while now and I'm tired in ways that rest doesn't seem to fix.",
        "There were years when I believed that suffering was proportional to virtue — that the harder I suffered, the better a person I was. I've had to dismantle that belief. Suffering is just suffering. It doesn't make me better. I want things to be different and the wanting is exhausting.",
        "I've started noticing when I'm enjoying something and letting myself enjoy it — fully, without commentary, without the concurrent voice noting that I don't deserve this, that it won't last. Just letting the enjoyment be. I'm not where I want to be but I'm still moving, slowly, in the direction of something better.",
        "The relationship between what I've done and what I'm worth has been one of the more costly confusions of my life. They were always separate things. Untangling them has been the work of years. I wish I could explain it in a way that made sense to people who haven't felt this same thing.",
        "I've stopped categorising my feelings about myself as things to fix immediately. Some of them are just feelings, and feelings can be held and observed and let pass. Not every uncomfortable feeling about myself requires an intervention. I keep trying to find another way through and sometimes I get close and then it slips again.",
